## Project Structure

```
ai-platform/
├── backend/
│   ├── app/
│   │   ├── api/           # FastAPI routers
│   │   ├── core/          # Config, auth, dependencies
│   │   ├── db/            # SQLAlchemy models, session
│   │   ├── schemas/       # Pydantic schemas
│   │   ├── services/      # Business logic (chat, rag, agents)
│   │   ├── workers/       # Celery tasks
│   │   └── main.py        # FastAPI app entrypoint
│   ├── alembic/           # DB migrations
│   ├── tests/
│   ├── pyproject.toml
│   └── Dockerfile
├── frontend/
│   ├── app/               # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── components/
│   ├── lib/
│   └── package.json
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Cursor.md              # This file
├── PROJECT_PLAN.md        # The phase-by-phase build plan
└── README.md
```

When adding new files, follow this layout. Do not create top-level files in the project root unless they're truly project-wide (configs, READMEs, compose files).

